ref: 5633 *taḍati2 ʻ stretches ʼ. 2. *taḍḍati. 3. tāḍayati2 ʻ (math.) multiplies ʼ Apte. [√*taḍ2]
Pk. taḍia -- ʻ spread out ʼ, taḍiṇa -- ʻ sparse ʼ;
P. taṛṇā ʻ to be stretched ʼ;
N. tarnu ʻ to make ready for slaughter (by pulling an animal's head forward so that the neck is stretched out) ʼ, tarkanu ʻ to be strained ʼ;
A. tariba ʻ to open, spread (a net or curtain) ʼ, ṭarāiba ʻ to spread, extend ʼ.
